PREAMBLE

This license governs the use of software, source code, web applications,
and any creative or functional works developed by or with the assistance
of artificial intelligence tools ("AI-assisted works"), authored under
the Hyggshi-os-website project. By using, copying, modifying, or
distributing any covered work, you accept all terms herein.

In the event of any conflict between sections of this license, the more
specific provision shall govern over the more general one. Where
ambiguity remains, terms shall be interpreted in the manner most
consistent with the Preamble and the copyright holder's stated intent
to permit free non-commercial use while protecting the integrity and
identity of the original Covered Work.

1. DEFINITIONS

   a. "Software" refers to any source code, compiled binaries, scripts,
      assets, or logic files distributed under this license.

   b. "Web Application" (Web App) refers to any browser-based or
      server-side application, including but not limited to websites,
      progressive web apps (PWAs), APIs, dashboards, and online tools,
      distributed or derived from works under this license.

   c. "AI-Assisted Work" refers to any software, web app, text, design,
      logic, or creative output generated in whole or in part with the
      assistance of artificial intelligence tools (e.g., large language
      models, code generators, image generators), where the original
      prompting, direction, curation, or integration was performed by
      the copyright holder.

   d. "Covered Work" means the Software, Web Application, AI-Assisted
      Work, or any combination or derivative thereof, distributed under
      this license.

   e. "Non-Commercial" means not primarily intended for, or directed
      toward, commercial advantage or monetary compensation. A work is
      commercial if it generates revenue, subscription fees, advertising
      income, or any other monetary benefit, whether directly or
      indirectly.

   f. "Competing Web Service" means a web application or hosted service
      that satisfies ALL THREE of the following criteria:
        (i)   serves the same primary use case as the Covered Work;
        (ii)  replicates 60% or more of the Covered Work's documented
              Core Feature Set (as defined in Section 1(g) and published
              at the official project repository); AND
        (iii) is made publicly accessible, whether offered free of
              charge or for payment.
      Visual or aesthetic similarity alone does not constitute a
      Competing Web Service under this definition.

   g. "Core Feature Set" means the list of primary functional
      capabilities of the Covered Work, as documented in
      /docs/CORE_FEATURES.md at the official project repository,
      versioned and date-stamped at each revision. The version in effect
      on the date of the alleged infringing act shall govern.

      If no Core Feature Set document has been published at the time of
      the alleged infringing act, Section 6(c)'s restriction on
      Competing Web Services shall be treated as suspended and
      unenforceable until such document is published by the copyright
      holder. The copyright holder's failure to publish does not affect
      the enforceability of any other provision of this license.

   h. "You" refers to any individual or legal entity exercising rights
      under this license.

2. PERMISSIONS

   Subject to the conditions and restrictions in this license, You may
   use, copy, modify, and distribute any Covered Work, free of charge,
   for Non-Commercial purposes only.

   For the avoidance of doubt:
   - Non-Commercial use of the Covered Work to create a derivative
     Web Application is permitted, subject to Sections 4, 6, and 8.
   - Where this Section and Section 6 appear to conflict, Section 6
     provides the specific governing terms for Web Applications and
     shall control.

3. COMMERCIAL USE RESTRICTION

   No Covered Work, in whole or in part, may be used in any product,
   service, platform, or activity that:

   a. Generates revenue, subscription fees, advertising income, or
      monetary compensation of any kind;
   b. Provides commercial advantage, competitive benefit, or business
      value, whether directly or indirectly; or
   c. Is offered as a paid web service, SaaS product, hosted API, or
      monetized web application.

   This restriction applies equally to Software, Web Apps, and
   AI-Assisted Works covered by this license.

4. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT

   a. Software & GUI: If you use any Covered Work to create an operating
      system (OS) or graphical user interface (GUI) — including in
      platforms such as Roblox Studio — the following credit must be
      displayed prominently in the product or its documentation:

          "Based on work by hyggshi-os-website"

   b. Web Applications: If you use any Covered Work to build or operate
      a website or web application, the following attribution must appear
      in a visible location (e.g., footer, about page, or credits
      section):

          "Powered by / Based on work by Hyggshi OS"

   c. AI-Assisted Works: If you use, redistribute, or build upon any
      AI-assisted output covered by this license, you must clearly
      indicate that the original work was AI-assisted and attribute it as:

          "AI-assisted work originally created by Hyggshi OS"

5. AI TRAINING RESTRICTION

   No Covered Work — including Software, Web App content, and
   AI-Assisted Works — may be used as training data, fine-tuning data,
   reinforcement learning feedback, or evaluation datasets for any
   machine learning or artificial intelligence model, without explicit
   written permission from the copyright holder.

6. WEB APPLICATION TERMS

   The following terms apply specifically to Web Applications derived
   from or incorporating any Covered Work, and govern where they overlap
   with the general permissions in Section 2.

   a. Non-Commercial Forks Permitted: You may build and publicly host a
      Non-Commercial Web Application derived from the Covered Work,
      provided that it:
        (i)   is distributed under this same HOSL-1.3 license;
        (ii)  includes the attribution required by Section 4(b);
        (iii) does not replicate 60% or more of the Core Feature Set
              of the original Covered Work (as defined in Section 1(g));
        (iv)  is not presented as, or likely to be confused with, an
              official product or endorsed release of hyggshi-os-website;
              and
        (v)   does not collect user data beyond what is strictly
              necessary for its stated function, and discloses any
              such collection clearly to users in compliance with
              applicable privacy laws.

   b. Paywall Prohibition: The Web Application must not be hosted
      behind a paywall, subscription gate, or any access mechanism
      requiring monetary payment.

   c. Competing Web Services: Building, hosting, or distributing a
      Competing Web Service (as defined in Section 1(f)), whether
      Non-Commercial or Commercial, requires explicit prior written
      permission from the copyright holder.

      For clarity: a Non-Commercial web application that does NOT meet
      the definition of a Competing Web Service under Section 1(f) is
      permitted under Section 6(a) above. The commercial/non-commercial
      distinction governs general use under Section 2; Section 6(c)
      imposes an additional, independent restriction on replication of
      the Covered Work's core functionality regardless of commercial
      intent.

7. AI-ASSISTED WORK TERMS

   The following apply to AI-Assisted Works covered by this license:

   a. Ownership: The copyright holder retains authorship and ownership
      of all AI-assisted outputs created under their direction, curation,
      or integration, to the extent permitted by applicable law.

   b. No Misrepresentation: You may not represent AI-assisted works
      under this license as solely human-authored when redistributing.

   c. Integrity: You may not alter AI-assisted works in a way that
      misrepresents their original intent or attributes false statements
      to the copyright holder.

8. DERIVATIVE WORKS

   a. Any derivative of a Covered Work must be distributed under this
      same HOSL-1.3 license. You may not sublicense under any other terms.

   b. Derivatives must preserve all copyright notices, attribution
      requirements, and restrictions present in this license.

   c. You must clearly document what changes were made to the original
      Covered Work, including the date of modification.

